Background

		Mr. Timothy P. Smucker, also known as Tim, served as Co-Chief Executive Officer at The J.M. Smucker Company from February 2001 to August 16, 2011. During 36-year career at The J. M. Smucker Company, Mr. Smucker held leadership positions at Houston Foods, as well as advertising and product development manager, Vice President of Corporate Planning and Executive Vice President of Operations at The J. M. Smucker Company. He has been the Chairman of The J.M. Smucker Company ... since 1987. Mr. Smucker has been Director of Hallmark Cards, Inc. since June 30, 2005. He has been a Director of Dreyer's Grand Ice Cream Holdings Inc. since 1997. Mr. Smucker has been co-Director since February 2001. He has been a Director of Earthgrains Bakery Group, Inc. since 2001. Mr. Smucker served as a Member of the Board of Governors at GS1 US. He has been Chairman Emeritus and Non-Employee Director of The J. M. Smucker Company since May 1, 2016. Mr. Smucker served as a Director of Huntington BancShares Incorporated, a regional bank holding company. He serves as a Trustee of The Ohio State University. He served as an Executive Director of The J. M. Smucker Company from October 1973 to May 1, 2016. He serves as a Member of the Advisory Board at ShareThis, Inc. He served as a Director of Grocery Manufacturers Association. Throughout his career, Mr. Smucker has been recognized with numerous awards and honors including the William H. Albers Award from the Food Marketing Institute, the Watson Rogers Award from the Association of Sales and Marketing Companies and Ohio's BEST Leadership Award. Mr. Smucker graduated from The College of Wooster in 1967 with a Bachelor's Degree in Economics and later earned his Master's Degree in Business Administration from the University of Pennsylvania's Wharton School of Commerce & Finance.Read Full Background




