The J.M. Smucker Co.Brothers Richard, left, and Tim Smucker are Co-CEOs of the J.M. Smucker Co. in Orrville. This 2008 photo was taken after the company bought the Folgers Coffee Co. from Procter & Gamble Co. in Cincinnati.
This regular feature tracks 2011 executive compensation at publicly traded companies in Northeast Ohio. 
J.M. Smucker Co. 
Headquarters: One Strawberry Lane, Orrville 
Business: Manufacturer and distributor of top-selling brands of jam, peanut butter, cooking oil, baking products and coffee. 


Chairman of the Board and Co-Chief Executive Officer Timothy P. Smucker $5,210,094.00 


Change from previous year: -23.7 
Executive Chairman and Co-Chief Executive Officer Richard K. Smucker $5,488,384.00 


Change from previous year: -31.2 
In fiscal 2011, Timothy Smucker, 67, was paid a base salary of $853,000; a bonus of $17,060; stock awards of $2,345,750; non-equity incentive compensation of $1,053,500; pension and deferred compensation earnings of $892,439; and other compensation valued at $48,345. 
Richard Smucker, 63, was paid a base salary of $853,000; a bonus of $17,060; stock awards of $2,475,000; non-equity incentive compensation of $1,053,500; pension and deferred compensation earnings of $1,032,317; and other compensation valued at $57,507. 
(Although their base salaries rose 4 percent, their total compensation packages declined because other pay categories fell.) 
The other compensation category includes: company payments to defined contribution pension plans, life insurance and accidental death and dismemberment insurance premiums; personal use of the company's aircraft; reimbursement of club dues and expenses; annual physical examinations; financial and tax planning assistance; and tickets to entertainment venues. 
The company's board of directors "strongly urges" both Smuckers and their families to use the company's aircraft for all air travel "for efficiency and security purposes." 


